pulses.name: Threat Intel Report - W10-2025
pulses.description:
These are weekly base recommendations to all IT Administrators and CISOs to take corrective actions to upgrade their security infrastructure against newly identified threats and attacks in this week. 

Security is a continuous process, and it has to be reviewed and audited on a continuous manner through manual or automated tools. 

These details may be used as an additional layer to verify the current security posture of an organization against latest cyber trends.

pulses.name: 20241104 Most Active Threat Indicators
pulses.description:
04 Nov 2024 : Most Active Threat Indicators
#Cybersecurity #Cyberattack #RCE #Botnet #IOC

Top 3 Source Countries:

- China (CN): The leading source of cyber attacks, particularly involving the Mozi botnet and various command execution vulnerabilities, indicating a focus on exploiting network devices and web applications.
- India (IN): Actively engaged in multiple attacks, especially targeting routers with command injection vulnerabilities and utilizing the Mozi botnet, showcasing a diverse range of cyber threats from this region.
- United States (US): Involved in numerous attacks, including the use of SystemBC botnet and various web application vulnerabilities, reflecting a significant presence in exploiting both server and application weaknesses.
